name: Vessels 116: Story Beat 001
description:
2) Tighter on the figure on top of the rock. It’s an old man – a WARLOCK - hunched forward with his head down in the face of the onslaught of spray from the waves that are battering his island. He’s dressed in entirely in black robes and soaked to the skin; it’s clear he’s almost skeletally thin beneath his clothes. He is holding out his hands towards the waves with his bony fingers splayed apart, like he expects to be able to feel something radiating up from beneath the water. He is shouting something, but his voice is almost lost under the din of the furious sea.
WARLOCK: …KINGS OF THE AIRLESS CHOKING DEPTHS! LORDS OF THE PRESSING, CRUSHING DARKNESS. MASTERS OF EVERY WRITHING, SQUIRMING CREATURE THAT DWELLS IN THE ABYSS…
3) Tighter. The WARLOCK suddenly throws his arms into the air, arching himself backwards and screaming up into the sky. 
WARLOCK: -HEAR ME NOW!
